Article in the Daily Economy
This year, the average Christmas basket of Napi in the Budapest shopping triangle increased by 16 percent, but each hypermarket showed an increase of well over 1,000 forints.
Since prices in food stores had already "climbed" in December last year, there was no more drastic increase in prices as a percentage of the previous high base price.
