The European Development Bank (EDB) approved a budgetary framework of EUR 300 million for the Hungarian financing of transport and environmental projects under Cohesion Fund support in 2006, of which 100 million were already under contract, and the contract signed now concerns the use of the remaining EUR 200 million.
