What kind of insurance is good for me?
Motor insurance, which provides security, is a significant expense for the car owner in relation to various accidents and depends on a number of factors, such as age, gender, date of licence, marital status, type and use of the car to be insured.
Getting the car is just the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car you want.
First, we need to understand what it is.
Motor insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract which states that the insurance company will assume the fixed insurance premium for compensation in the event of the accident.
The insurance premium is in practice the amount paid for the insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors such as age, gender, date of licence, marital status, type of car to be insured, use, etc.
Insurance companies determine the insurance premium on the basis of statistics, i.e. the higher amount is paid by the person who has a higher risk of accident.
That's why people over 25 or women pay less because statistics show they're less at risk because they're more careful.
Similarly, the insurance companies have found that married people cause fewer accidents than single people.
The frequency is the key to the type of use of the car.
The more frequent the use, the greater the chance of an accident.
The insurance companies take into account a number of factors when determining the premium.
The owner must therefore do a thorough research to be able to choose the most appropriate form of insurance for his profile.
The following are the most important factors in choosing the best option to meet your insured needs and to establish an acceptable price.
When taking out an insurance policy, people under 25 have to face a number of disadvantages, such as lack of driving experience and the fact that their driving licence is not yet valid.
While it is ideal to be protected against all dangers, there are more economical solutions.
More cautious drivers can take out full insurance against the risks and the costs.
In this type of contract, the insured person pays a part of the damage.
"The amount of the premium paid by the insured depends on the premium; the higher the premium, the lower the premium", says Luis Noguera, head of First Europa, the Spanish online insurance broker.
The other option is extended third party liability insurance, where the customer insures himself against damage caused to others but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, you'll be covered against theft, fire damage and loss of the car.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25, be careful and avoid accidents if possible, as this will affect your bonus and may reduce your future payments.
The bonus is the discount given to the insurance company in relation to the basic rate.
And the penalty that is levied against the basic rate is called a malus.
'The amount of the bonus and the discount depends on the insurance company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonus rate", explains Noguera.
Once the age limit of 25 years has been reached, it is easier for owners to take out adequate insurance, as the risk of accidents decreases as a result of the experience gained over the years.
We suggest you take out a full insurance policy.
"Young people are usually not yet able to apply their experience properly in an accident, even when driving", says the director of the European Insurance Company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when drivers have overcome the fear of beginners.
If you are already married but do not have children, it is best to take out full insurance, of course if your financial situation allows it.
Insurance companies consider couples with children to be the least risky customers, so the premium they pay is lower.
In this case, it is best to have full insurance for your own part (up to €300) or, if you have a higher bonus, to extend the insurance coverage from the third year of the vehicle to cover damage caused to others.
"They drive more comfortably, but they also have more purchasing power and can afford to have a higher self-esteem", confirms Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, we offer full insurance with a personal contribution (around EUR 150) or, if the bonus is higher, liability insurance.
Car insurance is very important not only because it protects the owner in the event of accidents, but also because it is a large expense, so it is essential to choose the right form of insurance.
