Three former employees of the Greenwich NatWest branch of the Royal Bank of Scotland Group have become known in the UK during a two-year extradition procedure.
The investigation into the Enron collapse in 2001 is still pending in the United States.
The first indictment against them in 2002 alerted Fastow to being one of the targets of a government investigation into the Enron bankruptcy.
