The British three were arrested three months later.
Fastow is currently serving a six-year sentence in a federal prison in Louisiana.
Copper is serving three years and one month in a Texas state prison.
The three Englishmen were each granted bail of $1 million to travel to the United States, where they will remain for the duration of the trial.
